snippet.textDisplay:
The first time I heard this track was in the Pakistani movie “War.” Since then, I’ve been in love with it. I never imagined that it would be an Indian song.

Today, I discovered the true meaning and philosophy behind this amazing song. Understanding its essence now, I realize how perfectly it was placed in the movie, deeply connecting with the scene.

Ali Azmat, playing the role of a patriotic politician, is murdered with this track playing in the background. What a profound connection!

Love from Pakistan 🇵🇰. Thank you for finding the legend Sawan Khan and producing this phenomenal piece

snippet.textDisplay: Really liked Sawan Khan manganiyar Ji here, Clinton ❤️, also in recent years haven't heard good amount of melodies in mainstream music, only they want to be have trendy music and not real rich music with good lyrics. Casual conversations type lyrics are used and trendy beats, unnecessary silly remixes are termed as film songs, this very time for Bollywood music is just terrible and getting more terrible with passing time,but some indie songs are saving our senses. Please use our rich cultural musics which we longed for several years. Also,can learn a lot as coke studio Pakistan season 14 , has set benchmarks with rich music blended with time, loved it, they are just cracking it, loved to hear that good music or better with such diverse richness in Indian classicals, and folks too with good compositions which we lack today so much using credible new talented artists💟
